definitions.definition: An artificial waterway or artificially improved river used for travel, shipping, or irrigation.
A tubular channel within the body or within a plant.
One of the faint, hazy markings resembling straight lines on early telescopic images of the surface of Mars; see Martian canals

main_definition: An artificial waterway or artificially improved river used for travel, shipping, or irrigation.
